quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,15,"And He hath cast on the earth firm mountains lest it move away with you, and rivers and paths that haply ye may be directed"
  16,16,And also landmarks; and by the stars they are guided
  16,17,Is there one who createth like unto one who createth not? Will ye not then be admonished
  16,18,"And if ye would count the favours of Allah ye could not compute them verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  16,19,And Allah knoweth that which ye keep secret and that which ye publish
  16,20,"And those upon whom they call beside Allahls have not created aught, and are themselves created"
  16,21,"Dead are they, not alive; and they perceive not when they will be raised up"
  16,22,God of you all is One God; so those who believe not in the Hereafter-their hearts are perverse and they are stiff-necked
  16,23,Undoubtedly Allah knoweth that which they keep secret and that which they publish; verily He loveth not the stiff- necked
  16,24,"And when it is said unto them: what is it that your Lord hath sent down? they say: fables of the ancient"
  16,25,That they may bear their burthens in full on the Judgment- Day and also some of the burthens of those whom they have led astray without knowledge. Lo! vile is that which they shall bear
  16,26,"Surely there plotted those before them, but Allah came upon their structures from the foundations, so the roof fell down upon them from above them and the torment came upon them whence they perceived not"